'''Frieda Lauth''' (1879 [[London]] – 4 May 1949 [[Durban]]) was a South African botanical artist who emigrated to [[Colony of Natal|Natal]] with her parents in 1882. She worked as an assistant at the Natal Herbarium and is noted for her illustrations of [[John Medley Wood|Medley Wood]]'s ''Natal Plants''.{{sfn|McCracken|McCracken|1988|p=71}}{{sfn|McCracken|McCracken|1990|p=66}} She resigned in 1903 upon marrying Thomas Floyd, and later lectured in botany at the Durban Technical College.{{sfn|Gunn|Codd|1981|p=217}}

