The '''Gold Medal for Italian Architecture''', {{lang-it|'''Medaglia d'oro all'architettura italiana'''|italic=no}}, is a triennial Italian [[List of architecture prizes|architecture prize]]. It has been awarded since 2003 by the [[Triennale|Triennale di Milano]] in collaboration with the [[Ministero dei beni e delle attività culturali e del turismo]] (the Italian ministry of culture), and with [[MADE expo]], a [[trade fair]] for the [[construction industry]].{{r|artslife}}
Recipients of the medal have been:{{r|artslife}} {{ill|Umberto Riva|it}} and [[PierPaolo Ricatti]] in 2003; the [[Renzo Piano]] Building Workshop in 2006;{{r|archi}} Doriana and [[Massimiliano Fuksas]] in 2009;{{r|fuks}} [[Vincenzo Latina]] in 2012;{{r|cds}} and [[Massimo Carmassi]] and [[Università Iuav di Venezia]] in 2015.{{r|cds}} Four "career" medals were also awarded in 2015, to [[Mario Bellini]], [[Luigi Caccia Dominioni]], [[Franco Purini]] and {{ill|Francesco Venezia|it}}.{{r|cds}}
